
If you want to use Git to download Ramp (and future updates),
read this online [Getting Started - Installing Git][git] documentation.
The [Set Up Git][git-setup] document is also helpful.

On Debian,
apt-get install libcurl4-gnutls-dev libexpat1-dev gettext \
  libz-dev libssl-dev
apt-get install git

Initial configuration:  (use your own username & email address, obviously)

git config --global user.name "Alyce Brady"
git config --global user.email abrady@kzoo.edu
git config --global merge.tool vimdiff
git config --global credential.helper cache
git config --global credential.helper 'cache --timeout=3600'
git config --global color.ui true

git config --global push.default simple

